      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/6/62 ¶ Dear Mr Bentham. ¶  ¶ I am glad to learn, that the boxes pr Young Australian &amp; pr Great Britain arrived. Pray bear in mind, that I have run the risk of sending the magnificent set of Rutacea...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.06.24b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, ff. 59-60.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged; M's sister Bertha died on 7 September 1861. Bentham notes receipt of this letter in his diary for Sunday 24 August 1862 (RBG Kew, Bentham diary, Ms. 17, 1861-5, BEN).</p>
               </note>24/6/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Bentham.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad to learn, that the boxes pr Young Australian &amp; pr Great Britain arrived. Pray bear in mind, that I have run the risk of sending the magnificent set of <name key="Rutaceae">Rutaceae</name> pr <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Dover Castle</hi>
               </seg> under the care of the surgeon Dr Thomson, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">without</hi>
               </seg> having secured a bill of loading. The Dover Castle sailed end of March, must therefore now about be in London &amp; has probably already <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">left</hi>
               </seg> again before this letter will reach you. The 4. box went end of April pr <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Orwell</hi>
               </seg> under bill of loading.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have an other box ready for one of the next clippers. The cause of the delay in sending more as yet I have explained to Dr Hooker<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 22 June 1862. </p>
               </note> It will be marvellous if you finish <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name> by Christmas &amp; as my health is somewhat fluctuating I fear I shall not be able to proceed with the flora of Victoria as I have begun, because I could not well trust the specimens away on a seavoyage before having worked them up for the Vict flora and fear if you go on so rapidly I shall be obliged to abridge my writings extremely on Victorian plants so as to keep pace with you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have now at last after the passing of the estimates arranged, that the £100 for the [1] vol. are payable to your [order] by the Agent General of Victoria in London and the necessary draft goes by this mail to that Gentleman.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have sent you by this mail 2 new genera of <name key="Rutaceae">Rutaceae</name>
               <name key="Bosistoa">Bosistoa</name> &amp; <name key="Coatesia">Coatesia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Bosistoa">Bosistoa</name>
                     </seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">B. sapindiformis</seg>) was erected by Bentham in<seg style="font-style: italic; "> Flora australiensis</seg>, vol. 1, p. 359; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Coatesia">Coatesia</name>
                     </seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. paniculata</seg>) by M in B62.05.01, p. 26.</p>
               </note> They are established on imperfect material, perhaps you have described them already. The curious Eriostemon? cymosus will probably also be a new genus. If so you might name it <name key="Lachnostemon">Lachnostemon</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">APNI does not list <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Lachnostemon">Lachnostemon</name>
                     </seg> or <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Eriostemon%20cymosus">Eriostemon cymosus</name>
                     </seg>.</p>
               </note> That <name key="Cookia%20Australis">Cookia Australis</name> is an <name key="Ailantus">Ailantus</name>, which genus comprises dotless &amp; dotted species, I think I mentioned. I know 5 Austr. sp &amp; described 3<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 22 June 1862.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is there no possibility of receiving proof-sheets of your genera?<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> I long much for them &amp; could probably furnish additional information. In what <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sequence</hi>
               </seg> will you publish the Australian orders? This I would like to know, so that I may send you the necessary <name key="Calyciflorae">Calyciflorae</name> first. Your notes on <name key="Rhamneae%20">Rhamneae </name>please me much I have a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very large</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">set </hi>
               </seg>of them &amp; will work them up early without anticipating your publications. For such excellent manuscript notes as these on <name key="Rhamneae%20">Rhamneae </name>&amp; former ones on <name key="Dilleniaceae">Dilleniaceae</name> I shall always be truly obliged.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See G. Bentham to M, 16 November 1861, and G. Bentham to M, 18 April 1862.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will make haste in getting you in possession of the remainder of <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name>, but I would not advise you to overhasten the work, as it will involve very much careful inquiry into the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">limits</hi>
               </seg> of species which altho' fixed in nature require often great patience for us to trace. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I looked to day over my huge set of <name key="Swainsonae">Swainsonae</name> &amp; am sure it will be a weeks heavy work to limit the species properly, so that the student going with his guide book into the field could array <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">every</hi>
               </seg> form under its proper specific head.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Hooker sent me a small paper photograph of his, which I value much.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 22 June 1862.</p>
               </note> Would you do me the honor of sending me yours also?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray quote no <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">synonyms</hi>
               </seg> of mine, when not established by diagnosis, even altho' the names might have been printed.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Lucas (1995).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Upon a few new Thalamiflorous genera I have written to Dr Hooker.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No known letter of around this time to Hooker fits this description. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will it be best for me to keep additions to the species of the orders now sent (which since were got &amp; they are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">daily</hi>
               </seg> increasing) until I can get the proof-sheets or shall I send them at once to you?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours with</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>true friendship</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">If I had the proof-sheets these new species needed not to go at all, unless in doubtful cases, &amp; my supplemental notes on them would come to you in time.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
